reviews_data.review_text: Friendly and helpful people all around. I really appreciate their efforts.

I was told by the barista that a Flat White is a “plain Latte” which is not true at all. A Flat White has more concentrated espresso and less dairy. The barista told me I was thinking of a Cortado, which is also not true because a Cortado has even less dairy than a Flat White. She can’t help if she was taught that, but whoever taught her that should know better. Even though this place is right next to my hotel I’ll try another option next time because all I tasted in my drink was milk, which completely drowned the espresso.

If you want a “cute drink” that you can Instagram this place is for you but if you want actual coffee it’s a hard pass.
Bad coffee
Was my go to before work, baristas are super nice and coffee is really good. Only wish they had pastries like the main location

Ordered the chocolate chip cookie latte and banana pudding matcha and both were delicious! The pudding is made fresh daily and can be added to a variety of drinks. Excited to go back and try more of the fun drinks of the menu!

Went for a coffee run with my sister since we were in town. Pretty cute place with tasty coffee. I tried the oreo latte and it was good. Definitely not sickly sweet like some of the more "trendy" flavors at some coffee shops. Would recommend.
Great coffee and service. Support small businesses, avoid the Starbucks nearby.
Absolutely wonderful coffee and barista! Thanks Olive! Delicious gingerbread latte on a cold day. 🥶 Make sure to go here and not the Starbucks on the corner. Sorry Starbucks! LOL.

reviews_data.review_text: Good coffee and really nice baristas. It's inside the building, so it's not directly visible from the street. They're still getting settled, but so far very pleased and enjoyed it. Give it a try!
The coziest coffee spot with the most interesting and delicious latte options!

Brand new, hidden gem coffee shop! Great atmosphere with just the right amount of seating and a concise, yet broad menu of coffee options. The owner, Jasmine, was fantastic and made a great cup of black, cold brew for a guy doing a cleanse and normally needs some half & half! Check this spot out and enjoy all that is offered in this perfect place of coffee bliss!
Best matcha in the CLT🍵！They always have such amazing and creative seasonal drinks on the menu too ☕️ service is friendly, great atmosphere. What’s not to like?
Wildroots Coffee's pumpkin spice latte is my new fall obsession, and I love the aesthetics.
Love this place! The coffee is DELICIOUS and the atmosphere is amazing! I can't wait to go back.

I absolutely love their first location and was thrilled to learn of a location opening closer to me. Now I can enjoy my favorite coffee while I stroll around uptown. Jasmine and staff always have a humanistic way of making you feel truly welcome in their shop.

You have to try their seasonal drinks!

The best coffee in town,  hands down.  This second location off of Church Street is so convenient.  This one has a Hawaiian themed interior.  Fast, friendly service, and I always love the seasonal favorites!
Wildroots Coffee in Charlotte is a cozy spot with excellent coffee and friendly staff. The perfect place to relax or catch up with friends. Highly recommend!
Such a cute new place. Great coffee with great service. I'll be back!
So happy there’s another location for me to get my favorite latte in the city 😋
Stopped by Wildroots new uptown location.  I had a Honey Cinnamon Latte and it was amazing.
